{
  "page": "Mountain's skull",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Joshua_Cairosmaesterjuegotronos.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/7/7a/Joshua_Cairosmaesterjuegotronos.jpg/350px-Joshua_Cairosmaesterjuegotronos.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"350\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/7/7a/Joshua_Cairosmaesterjuegotronos.jpg/525px-Joshua_Cairosmaesterjuegotronos.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/7/7a/Joshua_Cairosmaesterjuegotronos.jpg/700px-Joshua_Cairosmaesterjuegotronos.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Joshua_Cairosmaesterjuegotronos.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Maester <a href=\"/index.php/Caleotte\" title=\"Caleotte\">Caleotte</a> fetches the skull from its box. Illustrated by Joshua Cairós. © Fantasy Flight Games</div></div></div>\n<p>The <b>Mountain's skull</b> is an enormous human <a href=\"/index.php/Bone\" title=\"Bone\">skull</a>, said to be the skull of the deceased Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Gregor_Clegane\" title=\"Gregor Clegane\">Gregor Clegane</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> The skull's brow shelf is thick and heavy, the is jaw massive. It looks as if it is grinning.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Recent_Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent Events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#A_Feast_for_Crows\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Mountain%27s_skull&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Feast_for_Crows\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Mountain%27s_skull&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Feast for Crows\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Gregor_Clegane\" title=\"Gregor Clegane\">Gregor Clegane</a> slowly dies after having been <a href=\"/index.php/Poison\" title=\"Poison\">poisoned</a> with <a href=\"/index.php/Manticore\" title=\"Manticore\">manticore</a> venom by <a href=\"/index.php/Oberyn_Martell\" title=\"Oberyn Martell\">Oberyn Martell</a> during their <a href=\"/index.php/Trial_by_combat\" title=\"Trial by combat\">trial by combat</a>, in which Gregor killed Oberyn.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos72.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos72.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc2.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc2.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc7.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc7.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> Queen Regent <a href=\"/index.php/Cersei_Lannister\" title=\"Cersei Lannister\">Cersei Lannister</a> instructs <a href=\"/index.php/Qyburn\" title=\"Qyburn\">Qyburn</a> to bring her the head of the Mountain once he is dead, as Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Tywin_Lannister\" title=\"Tywin Lannister\">Tywin Lannister</a> had promised it to <a href=\"/index.php/Doran_Martell\" title=\"Doran Martell\">Doran Martell</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Prince_of_Dorne\" title=\"Prince of Dorne\">Prince of Dorne</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc7.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc7.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>  as recompense for the deaths of <a href=\"/index.php/Elia_Martell\" title=\"Elia Martell\">Elia Martell</a> and her children, <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenys_Targaryen_(daughter_of_Rhaegar)\" title=\"Rhaenys Targaryen (daughter of Rhaegar)\">Rhaenys</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_Targaryen_(son_of_Rhaegar)\" title=\"Aegon Targaryen (son of Rhaegar)\">Aegon Targaryen</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc2.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc2.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> Qyburn has beetles strip the flesh from the skull.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc17.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc17.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> However, <a href=\"/index.php/Pycelle\" title=\"Pycelle\">Pycelle</a> had previously noted that maggots wouldn't eat Clegane's mortified flesh, and leeches died after feeding on his infected blood.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos72.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos72.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Mountain%27s_skull&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Dance with Dragons\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:452px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Balon_Swann%27s_welcome_feast_in_Sunspear_in_ADWD_The_Watcher_by_Jaydeewis.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/6/6f/Balon_Swann%27s_welcome_feast_in_Sunspear_in_ADWD_The_Watcher_by_Jaydeewis.jpg/450px-Balon_Swann%27s_welcome_feast_in_Sunspear_in_ADWD_The_Watcher_by_Jaydeewis.jpg\" width=\"450\" height=\"225\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/6/6f/Balon_Swann%27s_welcome_feast_in_Sunspear_in_ADWD_The_Watcher_by_Jaydeewis.jpg/675px-Balon_Swann%27s_welcome_feast_in_Sunspear_in_ADWD_The_Watcher_by_Jaydeewis.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/6/6f/Balon_Swann%27s_welcome_feast_in_Sunspear_in_ADWD_The_Watcher_by_Jaydeewis.jpg/900px-Balon_Swann%27s_welcome_feast_in_Sunspear_in_ADWD_The_Watcher_by_Jaydeewis.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Balon_Swann%27s_welcome_feast_in_Sunspear_in_ADWD_The_Watcher_by_Jaydeewis.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>The welcoming feast in <a href=\"/index.php/Sunspear\" title=\"Sunspear\">Sunspear</a>, presided over by the Mountain's skull. Illustrated by Jaydeewis ©</div></div></div>\n<p>The alleged skull of Gregor is brought to <a href=\"/index.php/Sunspear\" title=\"Sunspear\">Sunspear</a> by Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Balon_Swann\" title=\"Balon Swann\">Balon Swann</a> of the <a href=\"/index.php/Kingsguard\" title=\"Kingsguard\">Kingsguard</a>, contained in an <a href=\"/index.php/Ebony\" title=\"Ebony\">ebony</a> chest with <a href=\"/index.php/Silver\" title=\"Silver\">silver</a> clasps and hinges. A welcoming feast is prepared for Balon and his traveling companions, attended by Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Doran_Martell\" title=\"Doran Martell\">Doran Martell</a>, Princess <a href=\"/index.php/Arianne_Martell\" title=\"Arianne Martell\">Arianne Martell</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Areo_Hotah\" title=\"Areo Hotah\">Areo Hotah</a>, a dozen <a href=\"/index.php/Lord\" title=\"Lord\">lords</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Dorne\" title=\"Dorne\">Dorne</a>, Oberyn's <a href=\"/index.php/Paramour\" title=\"Paramour\">paramour</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Ellaria_Sand\" title=\"Ellaria Sand\">Ellaria Sand</a>, and the eldest of Oberyn's eight <a href=\"/index.php/Sand_Snakes\" title=\"Sand Snakes\">bastard daughters</a>: <a href=\"/index.php/Obara_Sand\" title=\"Obara Sand\">Obara</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Nymeria_Sand\" title=\"Nymeria Sand\">Nymeria</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Tyene_Sand\" title=\"Tyene Sand\">Tyene Sand</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Before the feast begins, <a href=\"/index.php/Maester\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Maester\">Maester</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Caleotte\" title=\"Caleotte\">Caleotte</a> opens the chest, and the the skull within rests on a bed of black felt. Areo Hotah observes the skull and thinks he has never seen a larger one. Doran commands that the skull be placed on pedestal, a column of black <a href=\"/index.php/Marble\" title=\"Marble\">marble</a>. Caleotte is too short to reach the top of the pedestal, so Obara grabs the skull from him and places it atop the column. A seven-course feast commences and continues late into the night, presided over by the grinning skull on its pillar of black marble. Spun-sugar skulls are served as dessert, which displeases Balon. After the feast is over, Doran retires to his <a href=\"/index.php/Solar\" title=\"Solar\">solar</a> to confer with his family, and Maester Caleotte follows behind his wheelchair, cradling the Mountain's skull as if it were a child.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In Doran's solar, Obara takes the skull from Caleotte, who leaves. Obara wonders why Gregor's head was stripped to the bone, when it could have been preserved in tar. Nymeria suggests that tar would have ruined the box, and says that Cersei would have nothing to gain by deceiving them. If <a href=\"/index.php/Robert_Strong\" title=\"Robert Strong\">another eight-foot-tall man</a> ever appears, Cersei would be exposed as a liar and a fool for no purpose. Doran notes that the skull is large enough to be Gregor's, and that all the reports he has received say that Gregor died slowly, in great pain. Tyene confirms that if the <a href=\"/index.php/Poison\" title=\"Poison\">poison</a> used by her father, Oberyn, broke the Mountain's skin, then Gregor is undoubtedly dead. Obara says she has never doubted her father, gives the skull a mocking kiss, and says it makes a start on their vengeance.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>This upsets Ellaria, who wishes it were an end, and says the Mountain's skull is no comfort for the loss of her lover. She disagrees with Obara, Tyene, and Nymeria's desires for vengeance, as it only results in an endless cycle of death. Doran comforts Ellaria, promising no harm will come to her daughters, and then continues the conference after she leaves.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Mountain%27s_skull&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:The_Sand_Snakes_and_the_Mountain%27s_skull_by_grandkhan.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/1/13/The_Sand_Snakes_and_the_Mountain%27s_skull_by_grandkhan.jpg/350px-The_Sand_Snakes_and_the_Mountain%27s_skull_by_grandkhan.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"459\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/1/13/The_Sand_Snakes_and_the_Mountain%27s_skull_by_grandkhan.jpg/525px-The_Sand_Snakes_and_the_Mountain%27s_skull_by_grandkhan.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/1/13/The_Sand_Snakes_and_the_Mountain%27s_skull_by_grandkhan.jpg/700px-The_Sand_Snakes_and_the_Mountain%27s_skull_by_grandkhan.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:The_Sand_Snakes_and_the_Mountain%27s_skull_by_grandkhan.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/index.php/Obara_Sand\" title=\"Obara Sand\">Obara</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Tyene_Sand\" title=\"Tyene Sand\">Tyene</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Nymeria_Sand\" title=\"Nymeria Sand\">Nymeria Sand</a> view the Mountain's skull. Illustrated by Grandkhan ©</div></div></div>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Qyburn</b>: I am sorry that it took so long. Such a large head. It took the beetles many hours to clean the flesh. By way of pardon, I have lined a box of <a href=\"/index.php/Ebony\" title=\"Ebony\">ebony</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Silver\" title=\"Silver\">silver</a> with felt, to make a fitting presentation for the skull.<br />\n<b>Cersei</b>: A cloth sack would serve as well. Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Doran_Martell\" title=\"Doran Martell\">Doran</a> wants his head. He won't give a fig what sort of box it comes in.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc17.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc17.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Qyburn\" title=\"Qyburn\">Qyburn</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Cersei_Lannister\" title=\"Cersei Lannister\">Cersei Lannister</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>A fine-looking box, no doubt, but many of those assembled here in the <a href=\"/index.php/Old_Palace\" title=\"Old Palace\">Old Palace</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Sunspear\" title=\"Sunspear\">Sunspear</a> might soon be dead, depending on what was in that chest.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Areo_Hotah\" title=\"Areo Hotah\">Areo Hotah</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>No one <i>saw</i> the Mountain die, and no one saw his head removed. That troubles me, I confess, but what could the bitch queen hope to accomplish by deceiving us? If <a href=\"/index.php/Gregor_Clegane\" title=\"Gregor Clegane\">Gregor Clegane</a> is alive, soon or late the truth will out. The man was eight feet tall, there is not another like him in <a href=\"/index.php/Westeros\" title=\"Westeros\">Westeros</a>. If <a href=\"/index.php/Robert_Strong\" title=\"Robert Strong\">any such</a> appears again <a href=\"/index.php/Cersei_Lannister\" title=\"Cersei Lannister\">Cersei Lannister</a> will be exposed as a liar before all the <a href=\"/index.php/Seven_Kingdoms\" title=\"Seven Kingdoms\">Seven Kingdoms</a>. She would be an utter fool to risk that. What could she hope to gain?<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Nymeria_Sand\" title=\"Nymeria Sand\">Nymeria Sand</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/Obara_Sand\" title=\"Obara Sand\">Obara Sand</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Gregor_Clegane\" title=\"Gregor Clegane\">Gregor</a> does look lonely. He would like some company, I'm certain.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Tyene_Sand\" title=\"Tyene Sand\">Tyene Sand</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Is that how it goes, round and round forever? I ask again, <i>where does it end?</i> I saw <a href=\"/index.php/Oberyn_Martell\" title=\"Oberyn Martell\">your father</a> die. Here is <a href=\"/index.php/Gregor_Clegane\" title=\"Gregor Clegane\">his killer</a>. Can I take a skull to bed with me, to give me comfort in the night? Will it make me laugh, write me songs, care for me when I am old and sick?<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Ellaria_Sand\" title=\"Ellaria Sand\">Ellaria Sand</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><a href=\"/index.php/Cersei_Lannister\" title=\"Cersei Lannister\">Cersei</a> sent us a head. We should send her back a bag of them.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-10\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Obara_Sand\" title=\"Obara Sand\">Obara Sand</a>, to <a href=\"/index.php/Doran_Martell\" title=\"Doran Martell\">Doran Martell</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Mountain%27s_skull&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Radwd38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.00</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.01</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\">1.02</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.